arlink broadband and mobile satellites in Low-Earth Orbit as of March 31, 2026.\n*   **Capital Expenditures:** $1,332 million (Q1 2026), $4,178 million (FY 2025), $3,498 million (FY 2024), $2,455 million (FY 2023).\n\n### 3. AI Segment\n**Financial Performance:**\n*   **Segment Revenue:** $818 million (Q1 2026), $3,201 million (FY 2025), $2,620 million (FY 2024), $2,961 million (FY 2023)\n*   **Segment Adjusted EBITDA:** $(609) million (Q1 2026), $(1,237) million (FY 2025), $347 million (FY 2024), $1,222 million (FY 2023)\n\n**Disclosed KPIs & Operational Metrics:**\n*   **Nameplate Compute Draw:** 1.0 gigawatt (Q1 2026), 0.8 gigawatts (FY 2025), 0.3 gigawatts (FY 2024), 0 gigawatts (FY 2023). *(Also 0.3 gigawatts in Q1 2025).* The text notes the increase to 1.0 GW in Q1 2026 was driven by bringing the COLOSSUS and COLOSSUS II data centers online.\n*   **Capital Expenditures:** $7,723 million (Q1 2026), $12,727 million (FY 2025), $5,633 million (FY 2024), $463 million (FY 2023).\n*   **xAI Acquisition & Revenue:** xAI was acquired in February 2026 and forms the basis of the AI segment. The segment\'s revenue is derived from advertising, Grok and X subscriptions, and data licensing arrangements. Specific "xAI revenue" is not broken out separately from the overall AI segment financials.\n*   **GPU/Compute Infrastructure:** The text highlights increased R&D expenses driven by the "depreciation of GPU hardware" and "cost of cloud computing and data center infrastructure expenses" as a result of AI data center expansions.',
